Description: Jar made of straw tempered Nile silt pottery with rounded body, blunt pointed base, short neck and everted rim, coated with red wash; grass remains in interior.
Curator's comments: Shape similar to Proto 87h2 in Petrie’s corpus of Protodynastic Pottery (1953). Marked F for Fort cemetery, excavated by John Garstang; for excavations see B. Adams, The Fort Cemetery at Hierakonpolis (London,1987), and page 227 for this pot.
Acquisition name: Transferred from: Victoria and Albert Museum
Donated by: Institute of Archaeology, Liverpool (Excavation Commitee)
